  "market_context": "ETH 1-minute in a downtrend with a series of down-close candles. Price produces a green retracement leg that struggles to close over the down-close candle series and simultaneously wicks into a prior short-term high, creating a low-confidence continuation setup.",
  "key_observation": "Two failure reasons stack: price struggles to close through the down-close series (consolidation) AND wicks a short-term high. This makes a bearish continuation untrustworthy and signals waiting for either a clean breakout up or a manipulation sweep of the low for a reversal long.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified expansion lower with a series of down-close candles and watched for a retracement vs. reversal reaction.",
    "Observed a green retracement leg that did close over the down-close series, but noted it struggled to close over and also wicked a prior short-term high.",
    "Concluded this is a low-trust continuation because two failure reasons (consolidation closure + short-term high sweep) are blended together.",
    "Defined two valid alternatives: wait for a breakout above the short-term high for a new bullish continuation, or treat the move as manipulation that will sweep the low and reverse higher.",
    "Watched price run out the low and looked for a V-shaped reversal as confirmation.",
    "Used the inversion (large candle range closing back through) as a substitute change in state of delivery, then identified an internal continuation with a clean candle closure for a long entry."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When a continuation setup has two simultaneous failure reasons (struggling closure plus wicking a short-term high), do not trust it. Instead, wait for a clean breakout or treat the move as manipulation and look for a V-shaped reversal off the swept low.",
